        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 24 at 6:14PM MDT by NWS Goodland KS</headline>
        <description>At 613 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 9 miles south of Thurman to 5 miles southwest
of Flagler to 10 miles east of Hugo. Movement was east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Strong thunderstorms will be near...
Flagler around 620 PM MDT.

This includes Interstate 70 in Colorado between mile markers 391 and
405.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

These storms may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM MDT for
east central Colorado.</instruction>
